34 WHEREAS, this proposal would not cost taxpayers any additional moneys; and
35 WHEREAS, this proposal would better allocate the resources of this state to meet the needs
36 of its residents.
37 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
38 members of this body urge the General Assembly to appropriate an additional $2 million
39 annually to the Georgia Home Visiting program to improve birth outcomes, reduce preterm
40 deliveries, and decrease infant and maternal mortality rates, in lieu of appropriating such
41 moneys to fund crisis pregnancy centers.
42 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
43 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
44 General Assembly's legislative leaders.
